PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779606369
OL,3,CSoc Dem's Daniel Ennis elected in
OL,4,CDublin Central by-election
OL,6,FThe protracted process of sorting and
OL,7,Fcounting votes began at 9am at the RDS
OL,8,FSimmonscourt in Dublin and the Galway
OL,9,FLawn Tennis Club.
OL,11,FSpeaking as he arrived at the count
OL,12,Fcentre, Mr Ennis said he believed he
OL,13,Ftopped the polls because "we didn't
OL,14,Fbend on who we were".
OL,16,F"It was just listening to people,
OL,17,Fmeeting them where they were, whether
OL,18,Fthey agreed with you or not," he said.
OL,26,@uD@ZOUvD@TO]xD@AOUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779606369
OL,3,CSoc Dem's Daniel Ennis elected in
OL,4,CDublin Central by-election
OL,6,F"I believe in the politics of decency,
OL,7,Fpolitics of hope and inclusion, and
OL,8,Fpeople wanted that on the doors. They
OL,9,Fwanted that positive approach, they
OL,10,Fwanted change, but they wanted
OL,11,Fpositive change."
OL,13,FJanice Boylan, Sinn Fein's candidate
OL,14,Fin Dublin Central ` the constituency
OL,15,Fof party leader Mary Lou McDonald `
OL,16,Ffinished second.
OL,18,FThe party's Galway West candidate,
OL,19,FMark Lohan, fared less favourably,
OL,20,Fwith 6.7% of first preference votes.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
