OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779606369
OL,3,CSoc Dem's Daniel Ennis elected in
OL,4,CDublin Central by-election
OL,6,FGreen Party candidate in Dublin
OL,7,FCentral Janet Horner, who performed
OL,8,Fwell after the party lost all its
OL,9,Fseats bar one in the 2024 general
OL,10,Felection, was asked about
OL,11,Foutperforming Mr Hutch.
OL,13,FShe said they had "firmly rejected the
OL,14,Ftype of politics that have been
OL,15,Foffered" and that had capitalised on
OL,16,Fpeople's real frustrations.
OL,26,@uD@SOUwD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779606369
OL,3,CSoc Dem's Daniel Ennis elected in
OL,4,CDublin Central by-election
OL,6,FShe said: "It is frustrating to see
OL,7,Fhow much of the media narrative that
OL,8,Fthe likes of Hutch captured and I
OL,9,Fthink the narrow stereotype of our
OL,10,Fwonderful, vibrant and diverse
OL,11,Fcommunities that we have in Dublin
OL,12,FCentral, that is maybe perpetuated as
OL,13,Fwell."
OL,15,FLabour's Marie Sherlock, who took the
OL,16,Flast seat in Dublin Central in the
OL,17,F2024 general election, beating Mr
OL,18,FHutch, said that they "heard a lot
OL,19,Fabout Gerard Hutch" during the
OL,20,Felection campaign, but "his vote has
OL,21,Fslipped".
OL,26,@nD@KOUuD@FO]zD@WOU{D@SO]|D@XOU}D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
